description:
Based on the AMAZING new animated series! What do you do when the world's evilest villains attack? Call Earth's Mightiest Heroes to save the day! In our first tale, CAPTAIN AMERICA and THOR face a threat bigger than BOTH of them! And in tale two, following the exploits of everyone's favorite arrow-flinger: HAWKEYE! Brought to you by superstar writer CHRISTOPHER YOST (X-FORCE) and incredible artists SCOTT WEGENER (Atomic Robo) and PATRICK SCHERBERGER (WORLD WAR HULKS)!

Digital reprint of Marvel Universe Earth's Mightiest Heroes #1: "Enter the Mandarin; Assembly Line".
name: Enter the Mandarin; Assembly Line

description:
In his first new Dawn comic in three years, JOSEPH MICHAEL LINSNER brings to life three classic tales as only Dawn can. 'THE SWORDMASTER'S DAUGHTER' shows a young Dawn inspiring Darrian to become a master swordsman. In 'SAMSARA,' Dawn learns that Death is never late for an appointment. And in 'THE WHITE PHOENIX,' Dawn shows Darrian if it is right to fight false friends by sharing with him a page from The Bhagavad Gita.

Story Titles

  • The Swordmaster's Daughter
  • Samsara
  • The White Phoenix

volume.name: Dawn: The Swordmaster's Daughter & Other Stories

description: MINISERIES CONCLUSION! An armored engine of vengeance stalks the jungle trails, following a rogue band of Viet Cong guerillas and a pair of kidnapped children. Doomed to become brainwashed killing machines, a hero some call Jungle Jim is their only hope.
name: Hellhole: And the Shotgun Sings the Song

description: EVERYONE wants a piece of Tommy Watts - at least the part that can give them super powers. But if everyone in America is a superhero, will that be a good thing...or the worst thing that could ever happen to planet Earth?

Bandette has so far been able to thwart the attempts on her life by FINIS, but Absinthe, the evil organization's leader, is more determined than ever to bring her career to a very permanent end. So annoying! Luckily, our beloved burglar plans to turn the tables on the Nabob of Nastiness! Who will she enlist to help bedevil the crime boss? What benefit will her mischief bring Inspector B.D. Belgique? Will Absinthe forgive Matadori's failure to eliminate our brave heroine? And what new horror does Absinthe unleash in order to ensure Bandette's demise?
name: We Will Quest, No?

description: While battling a rogue Manhunter, Aya is infected by a virus, and Hal and Razer shrink themselves to microscopic size to see if they can fix her...and find Kilg%re! Can they win such a small battle against such large odds?
name: Journey To the Center of the Aya

description: Who shot Chas Worthington? It's not like he hasn't pissed off his share of people who'd want him dead. But while outside powers threaten to hijack control of his fledgling trash nation, forces within the plastic province of New Texas conspire to tear it apart.
name: Nation Building Part Two

description: An official meeting of top German officials in a nearby town spells trouble for operations in The Sticks. But, something much worse is about to arrive.
name: Cry of the Wolf Part Two

description: Barek confronts Skybreaker, which leads to an uneasy alliance. Talutah, Barek, and Skybreaker band together for one mission: To kill Cutter before they turn on each other.
Season one builds to a tragic climax as the team discovers that everything they thought they knew about Amaranth is a lie.
Batman and Robin think they've solved the Riddler's latest brainteaser. But when they follow their lead to a nightclub, it's not the Prince of Puzzles who confronts them.
name: The Riddler's Ruse, Part 2

description:
Contents

  • Ginga Patrol Jaco Ch. 1 "The Galactic Patrolman Goes to Earth"
  • One Piece Ch. 714 (Caribou Cover Story)
  • Assassination Classroom Ch. 51
  • Naruto Ch. 638
  • Nisekoi Ch. 82
  • Toriko Ch. 241
  • Food Wars: Shokugeki no Soma Ch. 31
  • World Trigger Ch. 22
  • Haiky!! Ch. 69

name: No. 33, 2013

description: As Tess settles into her new life as a purely-digital being, she needs to make some adjustments. Emil Hamilton and his colleagues at STAR Labds try to ease the way, but Tess's obsession with Lex doesn't leave much room for anything else.
name: Hollow Part 1

description:
Lost in the psychedelic warzone of the Blister, Blue is saved by a mysterious, other-worldly creature -- 6GG, a genetically modified silverback gorilla with two enormous six-shooters. Now, with the Rebel WarParty, pedal-bike bandits, and Blues own army (the BXF) on their trail, the odd couple must make their way through the wilderness of this strange land on a quest of steel, blood, and thunder.

Written by Simon Spurrier (Marvels X-MEN LEGACY, EXTERMINATION) and drawn by hot new talent Jeff Stokely, SIX-GUN GORILLA is a pulpy mash-up of Western weird- ness and lo-fi science fiction unlike anything else on the stands!
name: Episode 2: Just Another Filthy Memory

description: Hey! Have you heard the news? BONEYARD IS BACK! And in a special, oversize issue, no less! Feeling inadequate next to Abbey's previous loves, Paris does what anyone would do: buy a self-improvement potion from Glump. How could that go wrong? Also, Abbey in a black mini-dress and thigh-high leather boots. We probably should've led with that.
As the weather warms, adventure calls. And no matter where our steampunk sweethearts flaunt their fine forms in the face of danger, that's where the hottest parts of the globe are!
name: The Edge of Empire: The Three Sisters

volume.name: Victorian Secret: Girls of Steampunk Summer Special

description: Time for a celebration as THE 99 welcomes three new members to the team! But then things start to go wrong. How can THE 99 headquarters be attacking each hero separately with a trap built to neutralize each gem-bearer? Can the heroes fight alone...against their own house? Could an old enemy be behind this specialized attack?

Remy, Harlow, Blue and Lazlo have finally joined up, and with Ripley the lioness, hunt through the American wastelands for Remy's brother Max. But when a simple scavenging expedition in Las Vegas almost ends in disaster, only a miracle can save them. Can the mysterious Korech and his female disciples be the sign they've waited for? Continuing the enhanced adaptation of Amanda Hocking's best selling novel HOLLOWLAND by #1 New York Times bestseller Tony Lee (X-Men Unlimited, Doctor Who), with fantastic artwork by Steve Uy (Avengers Initiative, JSA Classified)! Dynamite Entertainment proudly presents Amanda Hocking's The Hollows: A Hollowland graphic novel.
name: And Then There Were Five

volume.name: Amanda Hocking's The Hollows: A Hollowland Graphic Novel

description: This is a series of single-panel comics by Brad Guigar that appeared on a sex-advice Web site, Courting Disaster, where you give the advice.
name: Vol. 4

description: Antimony finds a class for Shadow where he can go unnoticed and meets a familiar face.
name: Red Gets A Name

description: Number Four is arrested on suspicion of child abuse while Raymond Nolan discovers that his wife has been working with The Holy Numbers. Aaron Doyle makes a shocking discovery.

From the Shuster award winning creators of Least I Could Do and Gutters comes a loving nod to classic fantasy novels that manages to flip the genre on it's head. Unlikely heros cut a swath through a fantasy world that is extremely familiar and yet very different. A naive elven hunter makes an strange friend in an undead warlock and the two manage to make both enemies and friends as they fight the good fight against the Legaran Empire.

Volume 4 of the graphic novel series Vincent Price Presents features classic gothic horror! One of classic Hollywood's most famous scary men, Vincent Price made a name for himself in classic mysteries and thrillers throughout the 1940s, 50s and 60s. Now Vincent Price Presents comes to Bluewater Productions as their 1st ongoing monthly series. The series will feature some of Price's films as well as developing new frightening ones with his estate. Welcome back to the macabre world of Vincent Price.
name: Volume 4

description: Apprentice Sorcerer Mickey and his trusted friends take on all challengers in a grueling sorcerer's contest--it's team against team in a magical Battle Royale! But the stakes are much higher then anyone knows: An evil Sorcerer has trapped Mickey's teacher, and he needs to win the contest to get him back. But things get complicated when Minnie Mouse and her team challenge Mickey for the most powerful prize of all...
name: Diamond Moon

description:
In an epic battle, Cail struggles against the demon juggernaut Halstein in the streets of Rome. When the skirmish is interrupted, Cail realizes that he will need assistance to take his opponent down. For that he turns to the infamous Dr. Faustus who takes him on a journey that leads Cail through many darkened corners of the Eternal City before he forces a final confrontation with his adversary.

The Ascendant is a tale of an escaped Duke of Hell who begins to feel remorse for his millennia of debauchery and cruelty. That guilt causes him to masquerade as a human and go on a crusade against the other escaped creatures that inhabit the earth, corrupting and harming its citizens. Cail, the Doge of the Darkened Reaches, knows there is nothing but Earth and Hell, so his struggles are aimed at making the earth a better place, even if but for a short time.

Crimefighter Bantam and his sidekick Little Pecker must save Cockham City from a deranged villain, The Jerker. And as if The Jerker weren't bad enough on his own, Bantam and friends soon learn that there's an even badder bad guy in town. Will they be able to save the city, or are they too...chicken?
In the 1970's two kids get the shot of a lifetime on their instamatic before witnessing a gang of tripping teens get slaughtered by a giant fish.

Chachi #1 is the only comic where you get to:

  • See Chachi the Monkey Start His Own Religion!
  • Penetrate the World of Celebrities with Content the Poop!
  • Get the Inside Scoop on the Next Big Social Network!
  • Be Loved to Death by Cakemother!

That's right folks, you'll get all of that and more in Chachi #1! Now how much would you pay for a comic experience like that? Other comics have sold for as much as 1 million dollars, but thanks to this special internet offer you can have all the excitement of Chachi #1 for the low, low, price of $1.99!

You can't lose, buy Chachi #1 today!

person_credits.name: Geoff Mosher
person_credits.role: writer, artist, letterer, inker, colorist, cover

description:
White is passion, a color that won't yield to even the slightest imperfection.

From manga artist Suguro Chayamachi comes BLANC, a collection of six very unique short stories.

A young man takes it upon himself to find a lost cat's home. Two delinquents bond after one has a near-death experience. A boy discovers the joys and pains of first love. One punk makes a dark decision to cover up his tracks. A familiar face has one teenager remembering the past. At a Yakuza funeral, loyalty to a friend struggles with loyalty to the whole.

Chayamachi's stories explore that which makes humans so imperfect: friendship, love, and heartbreaking regret.
name: Vol. 1

description:
Black is an expression, a color before which words can only hesitate.

Suguro Chayamachi returns with another set of short stories in her second collection, NOIR.

An unlikely friendship begins when a delinquent picks up a timid businessman stranded on the side of the road. Though they can't understand each other there is something they each gain from this new, strange relationship.

Later, a teenager hires out help to break up his ex-girlfriend's new relationship, but his new accomplice isn't quite what she seems. In Nazi Germany, an artist is caught in treason when his son drops a book of paintings. And in England, a street urchin is given a special job, and while it seems simple there is a dark secret to it that could mean disaster for his friend.
name: Vol. 1

description: Severely depleted by a mission gone wrong, the mysterious Department O find themselves sequestered for a diplomatic mission, with a twist!
name: Body Politic: Part One

description: When a father can't get the doll for his estranged daughter, he snaps emotionally and enters a pulp landscape where he has the power to do what he needs. This noir crash of a one-shot looks at how far you would go to make your child happy, and could you go too far?

In the face of tragedy is when heroes are born and miracles happen, and Gabrielle Giffords is nothing if not both. A terrible attempt was made on her life and we all stopped and took notice, waiting with baited breath for good news. She's been dealt a strong hand, but she has persevered and she is an American treasure. Learn who she is and where she's been, and take a glimpse into the life of the woman who America rallied behind and will continue to rally behind for years to come.

Floating BunnyHead, the disembodied cartoon rabbit noggin, Armless Bear, the massively magenta ursine amputee, Slicey, the piping hot piece of pizza, and Raptoro, the Saturday morning cartoon Piatasaurus, have just won a trip to Westland: a Wild West theme park populated by robotic cowboys. Instead of spending their vacation guzzling whiskey, shooting robot bandits in the head, and getting to know the dance-hall-girlbots, the boys will have to find out why everything has gone haywire and unmask the shadowy figure lurking behind the scenes.

Frogman is a not-so-super superhero who kicks, punches and shags his way through life, sort of fighting crime and sort of saving the day. It's got action, romance, jokes, puns, nerd-references and scenes of hardcore sex and violence. What more could you want?

Doctor Who is currently very popular within geek culture. But did you know that the character is not the first quirky doctor to adventure through time?

The mysterious Dr. Moses Nebogipfel arrives in a small Welsh town in 1887. The apprehensions of the simple rural folk eventually cause them to storm the inventor's workshop in an effort to avenge perceived witchery. Nebogipfel escapes with one other person, the sympathetic Reverend Elijah Ulysses Cook, in what is later revealed to be a time machine. After having been missing for three weeks, Cook returns, aged many years older. He talks about a journey that took the duo to the days of mankind's last stand against an alien invasion in the 41st Century, and even further into the future to a time when humans are no longer the dominant life form on Earth.

Originally written by a 22-year old H.G. Wells in 1888, "The Chronic Argonauts" is considered to be the first well-developed use of a 'time machine' in science fiction. It predates his more famous time traveling novel, 'The Time Machine', by seven years, yet has never been adapted for other media. While Wells' version ends with a cliff-hanger, New Baby Productions has expanded the story with an adventure that is influenced by the legendary writer's other works.
name: GN

description: "I'll pay you 10,000 to marry me right now." A wealthy and gorgeous man suddenly proposes to Magda, who makes a meager living cleaning an extravagant luxury apartment. He is Rafaello Di Viscenti, the owner of the apartment. Why would a major Italian businessman propose to a poor woman like me at first sight? Magda refuses outright, but that night, Rafaello tracks her down!
name: Vol. 1

description: Now translated in Spanish! METAPHASE is inspired by the real life and death struggle of writer Chip Reece's son, who was born with two congenital heart defects and Down syndrome. This preview is a glimpse of an upcoming graphic novel from Alterna Comics that will star Ollie, a boy with Down syndrome, who just wants to be "super" just like his super-powered dad. In the pages of METAPHASE, Ollie will show the world that individuals with Down syndrome can be SUPER too! Art by Kelly Williams!

No Service:

Mickey and Donald run into trouble when they try to buy lunch for Minnie and Daisy.

Yodelberg:

Mickey has to avoid any loud noises as he hikes through the mountains to Minnie.

Croissant de Triomphe:

Mickey rushes through Paris to deliver croissants to Minnie and her hungry customers.

Stayin' Cool:

It's a scorchingly hot day and Mickey, Donald, and Goofy are trying to stay cool.
name: No Service; Yodelberg; Croissant de Triomphe; Stayin' Cool

description:
Cul de Sac chronicles the absurdly wonderful adventures of the Otterloop family. Alice, Petey, Mom, and Dad live in the cookie-cutter suburbs not far from the interstate. Here, and at school, their day-to-day life unfolds with simple joys, tiny infractions, and wonderful moments of gentle bliss.

In this specially curated for kids collection, the quirky world of Cul de Sac comes to life for a new audience.
name: GN

volume.name: Mighty Alice Goes Round and Round: A Cul de Sac Book

description: A family drama unfolds as Maureen moves out of her father's home while her older sister serves prison time. Family duty and honor all come into play as the two sisters paths move further and further apart. Their father's heart aches for his family to reconcile. Can Maureen make it on her own? Ho Che Anderson's art evolves throughout the story as Maureen sees herself and who she can become without the many forces pulling her in different directions.
Sulky goes to the forest to find food and gets involved with cats and angry leopards while the other lizards are telling ghost stories by the campfire.

During the day, 20-year-old Clea is the boss's secretary. By night, she's Max's lover. She's been playing at being a cool customer to suit his freewheeling ways, but that's all over now that she's pregnant! Clea decides to break off the relationship so that he doesn't come to resent her for tying him down. However, once he finds out about the pregnancy he proposes right away!
name: Vol. 1

description:
Set in the continuity of the original series, this anthology fills in the gap between the first and second series of the gothic science fiction television series Space: 1999, offering an exciting narrative of events that occurred "between the scenes."

Back Blurb

The sci-fi classic series continues!

September 13th, 1999 --- when an atomic accident causes the moon to be blown out of orbit and hurled into the unknown, the survivors of the lunar base stationed there launch towards their destiny --- and adventures --- across the stars!

Set in the continuity of the original series, Classic Space: 1999 - To Everything That Was fills in the gap between the first and second seasons of the gothic science fiction television series Space: 1999, offering an exciting narrative of events that occurred "between the scenes."

This collection is a celebration of the Space: 1999 comics of yesteryear, reprinting the best of the Charlton Comics series, the British Look-In issues and Annuals, with remastered and unpublished works by comic book legends such as Gray Morrow (Man-Thing, Tarzan, Buck Rogers), John Byrne (X-men, Fantastic Four), Joe Staton (Green Lantern, Superboy), and more.

A labor of love, Classic Space: 1999 - To Everything That Was utilizes over a dozen rare Space: 1999 painted artworks, using many as chapter breaks. It is adorned by a previously unpublished Gray Morrow Space: 1999 cover painting, originally intended for the next issue of the 1977 cancelled Charlton comic series run and only seen in print in the late '70s as a puzzle, now beautifully restored!
name: Part One

volume.name: Classic Space: 1999: To Everything That Was - Remastered Works From the Comics Archive (1975-1979)

description: Join the Super Siblings in their very first adventure comic by Patrick Scullin. Scout and Banshee are a brother and sister with super powers. Scout uses his powers for good and his little sister Banshee uses hers for bad. What's more is that neither knows the others true identity and they have unwittingly become adversaries. Written for geeks and their kids Super Siblings is the perfect comic to share with the family.

The kickoff issue of Unseen Justice. We are introduced to Wyatt Stone as he ends his tour in the US Marines and returns home to take the home of his dying father. Stone soon finds out that working as the local correctional facility is more dangerous than he thought.

This issue of Zombie Spotlight focuses on Artist Tony Donley. Three complete Zombie stories now available on Comixology for the first time.

"Shelby". Nothing can keep these 2 survivors from their baby, as they fight through a Zombie horde.

"Date Night with Dehlia" puts the reader right into the action. You are the lead character in this Zombie P.O.V. tale.

"Chores" is the story of a family just trying to survive in peace after a Zombie infection. Who is a bigger threat, Zombies or other survivors?
name: Shelby; Date Night with Dehlia; Chores

description: Questions about Cain and Abel, aliens, dinosaurs, and life after death.

volume.name: 101 Questions About the Bible and Christianity

description: Comic book that provides biblically informed responses on questions such as "What does the Bible say about the end of the world, what about angels and demons, do pets and animals go to heaven?"

volume.name: 101 Questions About the Bible and Christianity

description: How do we know the resuurection is true? What is the Trinity?Who were the Nephilim?

volume.name: 101 Questions About the Bible and Christianity

description: How do we know that God exists? What does the Bible say about ghosts? Does the Bible mention the cavemen?

volume.name: 101 Questions About the Bible and Christianity

description: Daniel is taken as a young man to Babylon after the fall of Jerusalem
name: Exile

description: Daniel rises to power and his three friends face their greatest test.
name: Conquest

description: The king of Babylon begins to go insane, Belshazzar rules with Persians at the gates.
name: Madman

description: The Persians conquer Babylon and Daniel is thrown into a den of lions.
name: Kingdom

description: The story of God come to earth in human form, with a special section on the Wise Men.
name: Volume 1

description: The early years of Christ plus a special section on the prophetess Anna.
name: Volume 2: Deliverer

description: The beginning of Jesus's ministry, his baptism, the temptation, and the calling of the first disciples.
name: Volume 3: Temptation

description: The calling of the first disciples and the first miracles.
name: Volume 4: The Disciples

description:
It is the middle of the 21st century and Tokyo is expanding and filling the bay with landfill to make room for the bursting population. But suddenly Tokyo suffers one of its greatest earthquakes, and the landfill liquefies, creating untold damage in the newly-made urban area.

The members of Self-Defense Force Rescue Squad Four are attacked and murdered as they are sent to help. They start uncovering the mystery that killed their squad: with their first clue in the south-Shinjuku bar called Chicago.

What they're digging up is a plot of murder and destruction - one that wipes out nearly the entire squad and leaves its two surviving members, the fierce Rei and her cool, handsome partner Uozumi, in a fight for their lives.
name: Book of Self

description:
1. Welcome to Maynardville

2. Chicken

3. The Rain Chapter One

4. A Minor Altercation

5. In Lieu of Letters

person_credits.name: Bill Amend
person_credits.role: writer, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover

description: Welcome to Oddville!, the complete collection of newspaper comic strips by award-winning cartoonist Jay Stephens, best known for his animated TV series Tutenstein and The Secret Saturdays. Join 8 year old superkid JetCat on her misadventures throughout the weirdest city since Oz! Oddville! is chock-full of strange and wonderful denizens, including a ghost pumpkin, a rude snail, a discarded bandage, and a gang of talking apples - all in spectacular full-color!
name: HC

person_credits.name: Jay Stephens
person_credits.role: writer, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover

description: Six classic stories of faith from the Old Testament are retold for a new audience - The Beginning, Moses, Exodus, Samson, Esther, and Elijah.
name: GN

description:
The Muses of Greek Mythology have brought tales and wonder to the world for centuries.

Follow this brand-new and exciting series that details each Muse and the story of how they came to be. Marvel at the story of Terpsichore, the muse of Dance, as she travels to the mortal world and meets with one of the most famous and well-respected dancers in modern history.

volume.name: The Myth Adventures of the Muses

description: General Adzic prepares to launch a devastating and brutal strike against America's Army. Captain Reed faces off with enemy infiltrator Commander Belova on the island of Palisav as Red Coin terrorists create havoc in the modern city of Vestimprium. Reed and his Quick Reactionary Force race to apprehend the renegade leader and find more than they bargained for - Red Coin controls the city! Locked in a desperate battle with heavily armed forces, the team must rely on every ounce of skill and training to accomplish the mission and get out alive in America's Army #6 - The Coming Storm.
name: The Coming Storm

description: The cult hit of 2012 is finally collected! After Jason and his team of programmers get stuck in their virtual reality game, Dungeon Lords, they must find a way back to the real world. Unknown to them, the fantasy characters they inhabit have taken control of their bodies - and now wizards and warriors run free in Las Vegas!
name: TPB

description: The Fairies have invaded and Merlin sends out the call for the knights of England. Unfortunately, The Order of Dagonet answers. Now these celebrity knights must face off against the forces of a magical world with only their wits to preserve them. The world is in a lot of trouble!
name: TPB

description:
It's another sidesplitting series of adventures as America's most popular cartoon family returns to the big colorful comic pages in this latest addition to the bestselling Simpsons anthologies.

In Simpsons Comics Strike Back, Groening fans are treated to another laugh-fest as they catch up on the latest antics of this irrepressibly irreverent family. First, it's a yuck-filled yarn of yore when Grampa Simpson reminisces about the good old days of the Depression. Then Patty and Selma take to the air as flight attendants, and the friendly skies will never be the same. Next, the network wars have come to town, and the big boys are running scared from the BBC -- the Bart Broadcasting Channel. Then last, but certainly not least, it's an epic brawl as the Presidential Fitness Program dispatches McBain to Springfield to whip the cholesterol-clogged town into shape. Between him and success, however, is hungry Homer Simpson.

When the TV show just isn't enough, fans turn to the comic books to satiate their Simpsons addiction. A veritable bonanza of the characteristic wit that made the series an international hit, this anthology will be a treasured gift for all fans of Bart, Lisa, Maggie, Homer and Marge.
name: TPB

description: This is your chance to legally double dip and score a double dose of one-liners and insanity! In Jesus Goes to School, witness the 31st coming of Jesus and the return of the abomination that is Ms. Tiedman. Lightning, locusts, frogs, and a wonderful lemon butter recipe with a dash of blasphemy ask and ye shall receive! Can Jesus Christ survive public school long enough to pass judgment? In the Really Really Evil Machine, follow the adventures of Max, Kindergoths new nemesis and first openly Asian character, as he tries to complete his REALLY REALLY EVIL MACHINE. How will Max accomplish his plans of world domination using refuse from a frat house kegger, a toilet plunger and a tuber? What could possibly go wrong? Both stories for less money than you spend at Starbucks! - See more at: http://digital.comicsplusapp.com/series_comic_details.php?product_id=com.iversecomics.allegory.kindergoth.special.one.06292013#sthash.fljmn5i4.dpuf
name: Jesus Goes To School; The Really Really Evil Evil Machine
You're Our Kind of Dog, Snoopy

description: Poopy Claws is a short, sweet, gross, funny, all-ages graphic novel about a boy and his best friend, a cat named Stinky. Stinky doesn't use his litter box or doesn't clean his paws. The boy's mom is a bit of a clean freak. And the moms overbearing aunt is coming for dinner.

volume.name: Captain Underpants Extra-Crunchy Book O' Fun

description: TEMPLATE is an action thriller with cyberpunk flair. Centering on a private security organization called Oversight, the story chronicles their attempts to make the perfect android soldier. When the first attempt fails, they speed up plans to try again under the assumption they learned from their mistakes. It is at this point that the main character, Beta, is created. Over the course of the series, her development is followed as she explores her own personality and discovers what she can and can't do not being in full control of herself. See where it all begins as this edition collects Weeks 1-3 of TEMPLATE with bonus digital exclusives.
Collects Weeks 4-8 of TEMPLATE with bonus digital exclusives.
Collects Weeks 9-12 of TEMPLATE with bonus digital exclusives.

It's action aplenty as the star-spangled Avenger takes on - and is brainwashed by - the hate group National Force! But what shocking secret does its leader, the Grand Director, hold - and who's really pulling the strings? The answers will cost Captain America dearly! Next, Cap breaks into an impenetrable safehouse, clashes with the Punisher while investigating a mob hit, battles the grotesque Adonis and teams with Nazi hunters to right a decades-old wrong! Then, all-star creators Roger Stern and John Byrne take the helm, putting Cap through his paces against Machinesmith, Dragon Man, Batroc, Mr. Hyde and Baron Blood! But as Cap learns new details about his past, he mulls a daunting future: Will Captain America run for president? Guest-starring Daredevil, Union Jack, Nick Fury, the Avengers and the Hulk! Collecting CAPTAIN AMERICA (1968) #231-257.
name: Volume Seven

volume.name: Post Presents Sugar Bear in "The Great Gold Robbery"

description: The most-talked about crossover event of the year is now available as a graphic novel! That's right; the Riverdale gang is crossing over with the teens of the hit Fox-TV series GLEE and musical mayhem is sure to ensue! When Archie and his friends, thanks to an invention of Dilton's, crash-land in McKinley High School, they're in for a surprise when they encounter teenagers very similar to themselves; teens who happen to occasionally burst out in song, that is! It's all fun and songs, of course, until the impending collision of two universes threatens the world as we know it. Can Dilton restore everything back to normal, or are our pals 'n' gals of Riverdale and the musical teens of Lima, Ohio doomed?
name: TPB

description: The Avengers scramble to deal with the threat of another Universal System as the New Adam's true self is revealed - and the most dangerous hero on Earth is created. As the Avengers face the World Breaker and discover the imminent threat to the Avengers World, the hidden connections between the events of AVENGERS and NEW AVENGERS are slowly revealed. What good is a White Event if it destroys the planet it was meant to transform? Plus, the Avengers discover Canadian super-team Omega Flight got lost in a Garden Origin Site - and learn why 'adaptation' is the scariest word in the Marvel Universe! Then, as Shang-Chi battles an ancient enemy, the Avengers... hang out in Hong Kong's swankiest casino? But they soon find out it doesn't pay to gamble in the spy business. Collecting AVENGERS (2013) #7-11.
name: Volume 2

description: When last we saw the gunslinger Roland, he was following the Man in Black's path to find the Dark Tower and set Mid-World right. Along the trail, Roland came to Tull, a sleepy little town in the middle of the desert where the Man in Black's sinister power had taken hold. Barely escaping with his life and leaving a pile of bodies in his wake, Roland arrived at the Way Station, where he meets Jake Chambers. Who is this sophisticated boy, and what is his connection to the world outside Mid-World? And is the Man in Black's flight across the desert just an illusion? Prepare for a tale of fantasy, horror, revenge and betrayal - a tale that could only come from the mind of master storyteller Stephen King. Collecting DARK TOWER: THE GUNSLINGER - THE WAY STATION #1-5.
